                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <gloss type="from">J. P. Morgan &amp; Company</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received March 28—2:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Attention of Mr. MacMurray.<note n="28" xml:id="d388fn28">John Van A. MacMurray,
                        Chief, Division of Far Eastern Affairs, Department of State.</note> We can
                    now confirm that British, French and Japanese, as well as American, groups of
                    Chinese consortium are not interested in financing Federal Telegraph Company
                    contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Morgan &amp; Company</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
